Q: Spring Boot @Valid returns just &quot;Bad Request&quot; message instead of my custom message A: <p>Spring Boot’s default error output uses <code>ProblemDetail</code> with only basic fields by default. To include custom validation messages, you must handle the MethodArgumentNotValidException in a <code>@RestControllerAdvice</code>.</p>
<p>If you just want one field at a time, you can validate manually in the controller using <code>BindingResult</code>:</p>
<pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>@PostMapping
public ResponseEntity&lt;?&gt; genShortUrl(@Valid @RequestBody Req req, BindingResult br) {

    if (br.hasErrors()) {
        return ResponseEntity.badRequest().body(br.getFieldError().getDefaultMessage());
    }

    ...

}
</code></pre>
<p>But global advice is cleaner and reusable.</p>
